      "writtenOn": "2019-06-18T04:02:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oops, yes, this is a race.\n\nWhile your suggestion sounds nice, I want to block Cmd.Start method until c.sess.Close finishes (unless ctx\u0027s deadline is reached), and it\u0027s a bit difficult to implement with the suggested approach. So this time I\u0027m sticking with doAsync. But please let me know if you have a good idea.",
      "parentUuid": "023283b4_ca564985",
